NAME

    assign - Enable Destructuring Assignment Syntax in Perl

SYNOPSIS

        my {$foo, bar => [ $x1, $x2, @xs ]} = $self->data;

STATUS

    PRE-ALPHA. Forget you've seen this!

DESCRIPTION

    This module enables a destructuring assignment syntax for Perl. Various
    complex data structure definitions on the LHS of assignment result can
    be used to unpack a complex data structure using variables that match
    keys and positions on the RHS.

